      <section eId="sec_CCP-3654">
        <num>CCP 3654</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3654__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the party who would be entitled to the possession of the immovable property
or real right therein in a possessory action has been in possession for one year after having
commenced possession in good faith and with just title or has been in possession for ten
years, the court shall render judgment in favor of that party, unless the adverse party proves
that he would be entitled to a judgment recognizing his ownership in a petitory action under
Article 3653(A)(1).</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-3654__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>In all other cases, the court shall render judgment in favor of the party who
proves better title to the immovable property or real right therein.
Amended by</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=111820</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
